          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A clear discrimination of the reactions was  made  by",
                " the use of a momentum balance method."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The nuclear   emulsions   loaded   with   Li-6   were",
                " irradiated with 32 MeV bremsstrahlung x-rays.",
                "The Li-6(g,t)He-3  cross  section  shows  a  peak  at",
                " Egamma =21 MeV with maximum value 5.1 mb.",
                "The angular      distribution     of     phototritons",
                " corresponding to the peak energy shows an  asymmetry",
                " around 90 degree, indicating an interference between",
                " E1  and  E2  absorption.  The  Li-6(g,pd)H-3   cross",
                " section has the maximum value 5.8 mb at Eg = 24 - 25",
                " MeV. The cross section of these reactions integrated",
                " up  to  32  MeV  are  12.8(1.9) MeV*mb and 18.2(2.0)",
                " MeV*mb, respectively. They make the total integrated",
                " photon absorption cross section to have a reasonable",
                " value expected from the E1  sum  rule.  The  present",
                " data are compared with the predictions of the models",
                " for li-6 proposed so far."
              ]
            }
          ],
